news.title: Barclays Bank, K Raheja Corp ink Rs 306-crore lease deal for office in Mumbai
news.para: The financial major's India arm will be effectively paying a lease of nearly Rs 306 crores throughout the lease term for a total 64,000 sq ft office space on 32nd and 33rd floors of the office tower Altimus developed by realty developer K Raheja Corp’s subsidiary Whispering Heights Real Estate.

news.title: Grasim Industries Rs 4,000-crore rights issue over subscribed
news.para: The company has received a cumulative bid for nearly 4.34 crore shares as against 2.21 crore shares offered by the Aditya Birla Group firm, according to an exchange filing.

news.title: Keystone Realtors posts net profit of Rs 29.88 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Keystone Realtors' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 533.33 crore in Q3 FY24 as against Rs 135.55 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit falls 7% to Rs 11 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Kamdhenu's total income fell to Rs 157.45 crore from Rs 183.17 crore in the year-ago quarter. However, it trimmed its expenses to Rs 142.43 crore from Rs 167.06 crore a year ago.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance targets $600 million India IPO: Sources
news.para: Private equity group Blackstone acquired Aadhar for about $300 million in 2019 as it bet on growing demand for affordable housing and financing in India.

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance's net profit up 69% to Rs 61.5 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Shriram Housing Finance's assets under management (AUM) as of December 30, 2023 grew to Rs 12,025 crore. The disbursals for Q3 FY24 stood at Rs 1,698 crore, up 70% year-on-year. For 9M FY24, its disbursals stood at Rs 5,289 crore.

news.title: Bengaluru: Court seeks data inventory of Shivaram Karanth layout
news.para: The court said to make the data which is in cloud storage accessible to the high court, the representatives of a private company engaged for the work of the committee should assist in downloading the data into the system (of the high court) and maintain and develop of the same for assistance in disposal of the cases.

news.title: Noida Airport's first phase development to cost Rs 10,056 crore
news.para: Goyal held a review meeting with officials of developer Yamuna International Airport Private Limited (YIAPL), a fully-owned subsidiary of Zurich International Airport AG, the concessionaire for the greenfield airport.

news.title: NGT seeks action report on sale of plots at Ganga bank
news.para: On November 7 last year, the NGT took cognizance of an advert stating “Residential plots with private ghat starting at Rs 25 lakh, NH 34 – 5 minutes” and directed the district magistrate to inspect the spot and submit a status report. The tribunal held this as a violation of the River Ganga (Rejuvenation, Protection and Management) Authorities Order, 2016, prohibiting construction on the riverbed.

news.title: Relaxation in development rules can't be permitted if it affects public safety: Bombay HC
news.para: ​A division bench of Justices Gautam Patel and Kamal Khata noted that the stack parking system in the premises of the housing society in Borivali completely undermined the fire safety and public safety not only of members of the society but also of children, senior citizens, and perhaps even passersby.

news.title: No illegal sand mining in Goa for past month, HC told
news.para: Advocate Norma Alvares told the court via video conferencing that there hasn’t been a single incident of illegal sand mining since December 12, when the high court passed its last order.

news.title: Third-party consultants part of Jaipur development body's land 'scam': Report
news.para: Officials familiar with the contents of the report said it called for a “proper investigation” into the process of allotment of land for most projects under the state government’s land-for-land scheme in the last five years.

news.title: Construction material, scrap take over pavements in Kolkata
news.para: According to rules, no one is allowed to store construction materials on pavements and carriageways. The KMC solid waste management department can seize the materials if they are not removed by the builders.

news.title: Four SEZs to come up off Yamuna Expressway near Agra
news.para: The YEIDA board, during a meeting on Monday, approved the project within a one-and-a-half km radius on both sides of the Yamuna Expressway near Agra. A consultant, said officials, has been directed to submit a master plan within the next two months.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Three-floor buildings with eight houses don't need final certificate
news.para: At present, completion certificate is not necessary for residential buildings up to 12m in height and not exceeding three dwelling units.

news.title: RR Kabel posts net profit of Rs 70.95 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: RR Kabel's net consolidated total income and gains stood at Rs 1,645.76 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 10.96 per cent from Rs 1,483.25 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Haryana: 100 illegal colonies on 500 acres razed, DTCP will now recover cost
news.para: In the last six months, the department carried out 70 demolition drives in which more than 100 illegal colonies — spread over 500 acres — were razed costing lakhs of rupees.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body gets Rs 3.20 lakh per sq metre for plot opposite Rajpath Club
news.para: This coveted Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) plot, just opposite Rajpath Club, shattered records, fetching the AMC a staggering Rs 3.20 lakh per square metre, the highest price ever for any civic body-owned land parcel.

news.title: Bankruptcy court approves J Kumar Infraprojects' bid for Pranav Construction
news.para: As part of the insolvency process, J Kumar Infraprojects has proposed to pay Rs 45 crore for the acquisition of the real estate firm against its admitted liabilities of about Rs 212 crore.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas Corporation posts profit of Rs 31.03 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas Corporation's net consolidated total income and gains stood at Rs 2,431.87 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 6.78 per cent from Rs 2,608.76 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
